# Ames Housing - ElasticNet Regression

End-to-end machine learning project predicting house prices using the Ames Housing dataset.

## What I did
- Feature engineering and missing value handling
- Scaled features using StandardScaler
- Used GridSearchCV to find optimal ElasticNet parameters
- Compared Ridge, Lasso, and ElasticNet performance
- Achieved R² of 0.91 on test set

## Best Parameters
- alpha: 0.1, l1_ratio: 0.9

## Model Comparison
| Model | R² Score |
|-------|----------|
| Ridge | 0.9166 |
| Lasso | 0.9167 |
| ElasticNet | 0.9171 |

## Libraries
pandas, matplotlib, seaborn, scikit-learn
